headline_main: Trump Was Impeached. Here’s a Recap of the Day.

abstract: Representatives Jeff Van Drew of New Jersey, Jared Golden of Maine and Collin Peterson of Minnesota were the only Democrats to oppose one or both of the charges against President Trump.
snippet: Representatives Jeff Van Drew of New Jersey, Jared Golden of Maine and Collin Peterson of Minnesota were the only Democrats to oppose one or both of the charges against President Trump.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The historic House vote on Wednesday to impeach President Trump on charges of abuse of power and obstruction of Congress was a mostly partisan affair, with only three Democrats joining with Republicans to vote “no.”

headline_main: Here’s What We’re Watching After Impeachment

abstract: Ignoring facts and trashing the impeachment process is no way to protect democracy.
snippet: Ignoring facts and trashing the impeachment process is no way to protect democracy.
lead_paragraph: On Wednesday evening, the House of Representatives impeached the president of the United States. A magnificent and terrible machine engineered by the founders, still and silent through almost all of American history, has for only the third time in 231 years shifted into motion, to consider whether Congress must call a president to account for abuse of power.

headline_main: Trump Has Been Impeached. Republicans Are Following Him Down.
headline_print_headline: The Republican War On the Constitution

abstract: The congresswoman, a Hawaii Democrat, called impeachment “a partisan process, fueled by tribal animosities” and said she favored censure instead.
snippet: The congresswoman, a Hawaii Democrat, called impeachment “a partisan process, fueled by tribal animosities” and said she favored censure instead.
lead_paragraph: Representative Tulsi Gabbard, a Hawaii Democrat and 2020 presidential candidate, broke with most members of her party on Wednesday and voted “present” on the two articles of impeachment charging President Trump with abuse of power and obstruction of Congress.

abstract: Here’s what we know about if and when President Trump will be tried in the Senate.
snippet: Here’s what we know about if and when President Trump will be tried in the Senate.
lead_paragraph: Now that the House has voted to impeach President Trump, the matter would normally move to the Senate for a trial — the third for an American president.

abstract: A majority of lawmakers in the U.S. House of Representatives voted on Wednesday to impeach President Donald Trump on a charge of abusing his power by trying to pressure Ukraine to investigate a political rival.
snippet: A majority of lawmakers in the U.S. House of Representatives voted on Wednesday to impeach President Donald Trump on a charge of abusing his power by trying to pressure Ukraine to investigate a political rival.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A majority of lawmakers in the U.S. House of Representatives voted on Wednesday to impeach President Donald Trump on a charge of abusing his power by trying to pressure Ukraine to investigate a political rival.
headline_main: Majority of House Votes to Impeach Trump for Abuse of Power
headline_print_headline: Majority of House Votes to Impeach Trump for Abuse of Power

abstract: The Democratic-led House of Representatives charged President Trump with abuse of power and obstruction of Congress.

abstract: A Philippine court on Thursday found key members of a powerful political clan guilty of a 2009 massacre in a southern province that left 57 people dead, including 32 media workers, in a brazen execution-style attack that horrified the world.
snippet: A Philippine court on Thursday found key members of a powerful political clan guilty of a 2009 massacre in a southern province that left 57 people dead, including 32 media workers, in a brazen execution-style attack that horrified the world.
lead_paragraph: MANILA, Philippines — A Philippine court on Thursday found key members of a powerful political clan guilty of a 2009 massacre in a southern province that left 57 people dead, including 32 media workers, in a brazen execution-style attack that horrified the world.
headline_main: Philippines Convicts Key Clan Members in 2009 Massacre
headline_print_headline: Philippines Convicts Key Clan Members in 2009 Massacre

abstract: From Capitol Hill to the Trump hotel to the White House, Wednesday was not a normal day, even in the not-normal Trump administration.
snippet: From Capitol Hill to the Trump hotel to the White House, Wednesday was not a normal day, even in the not-normal Trump administration.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — It’s not as if anyone was expecting a normal Wednesday to materialize on Capitol Hill. Presidents don’t get impeached every day, just like they generally don’t write six-page harangues charging Democrats with “declaring open war on American Democracy”(that was Tuesday) or tweet that Speaker Nancy Pelosi’s “teeth were falling out of her mouth” (that was Sunday).
